results.name: Decimal expansion of Sum_{primes p} 1/(p^2*(p-1)).
comment: Generally, sum_p 1/(p^s*(p-1)) equals A136141 minus the sum over all prime zeta functions with index 2 to s (see A085964 to A085969).
mathematica: digits = 104; sp = NSum[PrimeZetaP[n], {n, 3, Infinity},  WorkingPrecision -> digits + 10, NSumTerms -> 2*digits]; RealDigits[sp, 10, digits] // First (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Sep 11 2015 *)
